  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/18005351?book_show_action=true">Mar 18, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/900147-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780867609189" href="/book/show/955349.Taliesin">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/900147-laura?shelf=bookmooch">bookmooch</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/900147-laura?shelf=read-2010">read-2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/900147-laura?shelf=hf-ancient-europe">hf-ancient-europe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18005351" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12870343385186059571">This book tells simultaneously the story of the fall of Atlantis, the subsequent travel of Princess Charis and her family to Ynys Prydein (Britain), and the discovery and training of Taliesin as a druid-bard. The two eventually meet, marry, and Myrddin (Merlin) is born, just weeks before a tragedy brought about by Charis&apos; jealous half-sister, Morgian.</span>
  <span id="freeText12870343385186059571" style="display:none">This book tells simultaneously the story of the fall of Atlantis, the subsequent travel of Princess Charis and her family to Ynys Prydein (Britain), and the discovery and training of Taliesin as a druid-bard. The two eventually meet, marry, and Myrddin (Merlin) is born, just weeks before a tragedy brought about by Charis' jealous half-sister, Morgian.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12870343385186059571" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
